        public boolean isTransactional()
        Description copied from interface: Any
        Whether the implementation has transactional semantics. This method returns true if the implementation is prepared to take part in a transaction, false otherwise.
        Specified by:
        isTransactional in interface Any
        Returns:
        true if the instance is transactional, in which case it is submitted to the transaction when operations that are defined as mutating are performed upon it. false if the instance has no transactional semantics.

      • bestowConstness

        public Any bestowConstness()
        Description copied from interface: Any
        If possible, return a const version of this. This method may return this even if this is non-const, that is this method is not bound to return a const version of the instance or even throw if it cannot (at the moment).
        Specified by:
        bestowConstness in interface Any
        Returns:
        A const version of this. The return value has the same property values and behaviour as the original;

        this if the instance is already const;

        this if the instance does not properly implement constness, in which case Any.isConst() may still return false.
